§ 48-8-80. "Qualified municipality" definedAs used in this article, the term "qualified municipality" means only those incorporated municipalities which impose a tax other than the tax authorized by this article and which provide at least three of the following services:
(1)  Water;

(2)  Sewage;

(3)  Garbage collection;

(4)  Police protection;

(5)  Fire protection; or

(6)  Library.

